# cell-return-values

RULE: Every cell that defines a variable used by another cell must return that variable in a tuple.
RULE: Return statements are always tuples — even for a single value: `return (df,)` not `return df`.
RULE: Variables not returned from a cell are invisible to all other cells.
RULE: Cell function parameters must match the names of variables returned by upstream cells exactly — marimo injects dependencies by name.

**Correct pattern:**
```python
@app.cell
def _(mo):
    import polars as pl
    df = pl.read_parquet("data/raw/data.parquet")
    return (df, pl)                    # both available to downstream cells

@app.cell
def _(df, mo):                         # df injected by name from above
    mo.ui.table(df)                    # last expression — displayed as output
    return                             # nothing to pass downstream
```

