# displaying-plots

RULE: For matplotlib — use `plt.gca()` or `plt.gcf()` as the last expression, never `plt.show()`. `plt.show()` clears the figure and produces no output in marimo.
RULE: For plotly — return the figure object directly as the last expression.
RULE: For altair — return the chart object directly as the last expression.
RULE: To make matplotlib plots interactive (pan, zoom), wrap with `mo.mpl.interactive(ax)`.
RULE: To make matplotlib or altair plots reactive (selection feeds back to Python), wrap with `mo.ui.matplotlib(ax)` or `mo.ui.altair_chart(chart)` and access selections via `.value`.
RULE: Call `plt.tight_layout()` before the final expression if axis labels are being cut off.
RULE: Save figures to `FIGURES_DIR` from `{{ package_name }}.paths` — never hardcode output paths.
```python
# matplotlib — correct
@app.cell
def _(mo):
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(df["price"], bins=30)
    ax.set_xlabel("Price (£)")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.gca()                          # last expression — displays the plot
    return

# matplotlib — wrong
@app.cell
def _():
    plt.show()                         # clears figure, produces nothing in marimo
    return
```

