# layout-and-composition

RULE: Use `mo.hstack([...])` to display elements side by side.
RULE: Use `mo.vstack([...])` to display elements stacked vertically.
RULE: Use `mo.tabs({"Tab name": content, ...})` for tabbed layouts.
RULE: Use `mo.accordion({"Section": content, ...})` for collapsible sections.
RULE: Use `mo.callout(mo.md("..."), kind="warn")` for callout boxes — valid kinds: `neutral`, `danger`, `warn`, `success`, `info`.
RULE: Never use raw HTML strings for layout — marimo's layout components handle all common cases.
```python
@app.cell
def _(mo, fig1, fig2):
    mo.hstack([fig1, fig2])            # side by side
    return
```

