# markdown-and-text

RULE: Use `mo.md("...")` for all markdown text output — not `print()` and not raw strings.
RULE: Use f-strings inside `mo.md()` to interpolate Python values into markdown dynamically.
RULE: To embed a marimo object (table, plot, UI element) inside markdown, use an f-string and marimo will render it correctly.
RULE: For non-marimo objects embedded in markdown (e.g. matplotlib figures), wrap with `mo.as_html()` first.
```python
@app.cell
def _(df, mo):
    mo.md(f"""
    ## Summary

    Dataset contains **{df.height:,} rows** and **{df.width} columns**.
    """)
    return
```

